The possibility of the proposition is, of course, founded on the prin- 
ciple of signs as going proxy for objects. [Cf. 4.0312.] 

Thus in the proposition something has something else as its proxy. 
But there is also the common cement. 

My fundamental thought is that the logical constants are not 
proxies. That the logic of the fact cannot have anything as its proxy. 
[See 4.0312.] 

